msgctxt "mission/single/05-eng/1944_09_20_oosterbeek/name"
msgid "On to the End"
msgstr ""

msgctxt "mission/single/05-eng/1944_09_20_oosterbeek/name_big"
msgid "On to the End"
msgstr ""

msgctxt "mission/single/05-eng/1944_09_20_oosterbeek/outro_completed"
msgid "Everything that could have gone wrong in this operation went horribly wrong. Just now, we’ve again suffered horrendous casualties, but you’ve managed to make it out of there and live to fight another day. Market Garden failed due to ignorant commanders, not through a lack of courage."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "mission/single/05-eng/1944_09_20_oosterbeek/outro_failed"
msgid "This is awful, they gave us a right pasting. Operation Market Garden has failed, and now our retreat has failed as well. Now you have become a prisoner of war. Perhaps this was just one bridge too far?"
msgstr ""

msgctxt "mission/single/05-eng/1944_09_20_oosterbeek/date"
msgid "September 22nd, 1944 · Oosterbeek, Netherlands"
msgstr ""

msgctxt "mission/single/05-eng/1944_09_20_oosterbeek/place"
msgid "1st Airborne Division"
msgstr ""

msgctxt "mission/single/05-eng/1944_09_20_oosterbeek/story"
msgid "You have been in battle for 3 days straight, while the situation is getting worse for the British paratroopers in and around Arnhem.\n\nSince the resupply operation failed, things are getting worse by the minute.\n\nControlling the bridge has become impossible. XXX corps is still south of Nijmegen, fighting to get control over the bridge there. It doesn’t look like they will break through soon.\n\nThe units fighting west of the bridge are to retreat from Arnhem to the town of Oosterbeek. That includes you. Pick up any stragglers you might find and make sure you stay out of the hands of the Germans."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "mission/single/05-eng/1944_09_20_oosterbeek/ui/gameover_pl_dead"
msgid "You lost all of your units."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "mission/single/05-eng/1944_09_20_oosterbeek/ui/gameover_defense"
msgid "German forces have broken through."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "mission/single/05-eng/1944_09_20_oosterbeek/ui/gameover_timer"
msgid "The evacuation team has left without you."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "mission/single/05-eng/1944_09_20_oosterbeek/narrator/cutscene/intro_01"
msgid "Dammit, I’m empty!"
msgstr ""

msgctxt "mission/single/05-eng/1944_09_20_oosterbeek/narrator/cutscene/intro_02"
msgid "That makes two of us, mate…"
msgstr ""

msgctxt "mission/single/05-eng/1944_09_20_oosterbeek/narrator/cutscene/intro_03"
msgid "Cholerny Szwaby… Look at them, no shame, huh? They already dare to crawl this close to us."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "mission/single/05-eng/1944_09_20_oosterbeek/narrator/cutscene/intro_04"
msgid "You alive, yes? Good. Though, you look like ghosts, and… Boże święty, you smell like you've been buried already."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "mission/single/05-eng/1944_09_20_oosterbeek/narrator/cutscene/intro_05"
msgid "I have one good news… and one very shitty one. Good news is that you caught your last train out of this hell. Me and my squad, well, just the two of us left now, we look for poor boys like you to drag out."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "mission/single/05-eng/1944_09_20_oosterbeek/narrator/cutscene/intro_06"
msgid "The bad news is, if you take a quick look around… We’re surrounded by these skurwiele. Either we find more weapons and send Szwaby back in pieces where they came from, or activate our brains and slip past the patrols. Lucky for us, the night is dark today."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "mission/single/05-eng/1944_09_20_oosterbeek/narrator/cutscene/intro_07"
msgid "So… what do you say, huh? We find more guns and send them back to their Vaterland, or the clever way, like ghosts in the night?"
msgstr ""

msgctxt "mission/single/05-eng/1944_09_20_oosterbeek/narrator/part01_01_stealth"
msgid "Hold! An enemy vehicle coming from the south-east."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "mission/single/05-eng/1944_09_20_oosterbeek/narrator/part01_01_combat"
msgid "Watch out! An enemy vehicle coming from the south-east."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "mission/single/05-eng/1944_09_20_oosterbeek/narrator/cutscene/perimeter_01"
msgid "Szwaby are attacking the British outpost! We need to help our people."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "mission/single/05-eng/1944_09_20_oosterbeek/narrator/cutscene/perimeter_02"
msgid "Things became even worse. I recall the last outpost controlled by Brits was three hundred meters away from here. The rats are increasing their pressure and are not giving up."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "mission/single/05-eng/1944_09_20_oosterbeek/narrator/part02_01"
msgid "I’ll be damned! Kowalczyk, you made it out again! Bloody glad to see you, mate! I am really wondering how you manage to escape death every time."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "mission/single/05-eng/1944_09_20_oosterbeek/narrator/part02_02"
msgid "There’s no special secret, actually. I just say “not today” to this insatiable bastard."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "mission/single/05-eng/1944_09_20_oosterbeek/narrator/part02_03"
msgid "Thanks God you lads are still holding this position. Major sent us to support you."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "mission/single/05-eng/1944_09_20_oosterbeek/narrator/part02_04"
msgid "So you’re our reinforcements?.. That’s all?.. Cholera, Major is losing his sense of humor if it’s supposed to be some kind of a joke."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "mission/single/05-eng/1944_09_20_oosterbeek/narrator/part02_09"
msgid "A bloody tank from the east incoming! Our PIAT operator got hit. Lads, grab his launcher and destroy the tank!"
msgstr ""

msgctxt "mission/single/05-eng/1944_09_20_oosterbeek/narrator/part02_10"
msgid "O cholera… That’s a flamethrower tank! Kill it now!"
msgstr ""

msgctxt "mission/single/05-eng/1944_09_20_oosterbeek/narrator/part02_11"
msgid "Nice hit, lads! Let them taste their own weapon."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "mission/single/05-eng/1944_09_20_oosterbeek/narrator/part02_12"
msgid "I reckon that’s all of them… At least for now. So if you’ll excuse me, gentlemen, I better disappear before the Major completely loses his mind over how long I’ve been gone."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "mission/single/05-eng/1944_09_20_oosterbeek/narrator/part03_01"
msgid "I need to report to Major Urquhart about my return. He should be at HQ, in the hotel."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "mission/single/05-eng/1944_09_20_oosterbeek/narrator/part03_02"
msgid "Do you even realise what you’ve done?! The CO will have our heads if he sees this mess!"
msgstr ""

msgctxt "mission/single/05-eng/1944_09_20_oosterbeek/narrator/part03_03"
msgid "Still, it might be worth looking around. Maybe some lads could use a hand."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "mission/single/05-eng/1944_09_20_oosterbeek/narrator/part03_qf17_01"
msgid "I heard you people are arguing about something?"
msgstr ""

msgctxt "mission/single/05-eng/1944_09_20_oosterbeek/narrator/part03_qf17_02"
msgid "Just look what those idiots have done! Blew up the damn building and the wreckage landed right on the wheel of our 17-pounder!"
msgstr ""

msgctxt "mission/single/05-eng/1944_09_20_oosterbeek/narrator/part03_qf17_03"
msgid "Major say destroy. We destroy, tak?! We scream “Move away”. You stand like stupid cow and talk to wind!"
msgstr ""

msgctxt "mission/single/05-eng/1944_09_20_oosterbeek/narrator/part03_qf17_04"
msgid "Calm down, both of you. It’s not the right time to piss each other. Why can't you just replace the wheel?"
msgstr ""

msgctxt "mission/single/05-eng/1944_09_20_oosterbeek/narrator/part03_qf17_05_2"
msgid "Well… There’s one option, technically… Back on manoeuvres, we saw some wasted Canadians try swapping a 17-pounder wheel with one off a captured Opel Blitz. Sort of a wager. Looked ridiculous, and the wheel fell to bits after two minutes of towing."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "mission/single/05-eng/1944_09_20_oosterbeek/narrator/part03_qf17_09"
msgid "Do you think you'll get it done?"
msgstr ""

msgctxt "mission/single/05-eng/1944_09_20_oosterbeek/narrator/part03_qf17_10"
msgid "Worked for a bunch of drunk Canucks, why not us? Just get us the bloody wheel off one of those captured trucks and we’ll take care of the rest."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "mission/single/05-eng/1944_09_20_oosterbeek/narrator/part03_qf17_11"
msgid "Dobrze, let’s search for a szwabski truck."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "mission/single/05-eng/1944_09_20_oosterbeek/narrator/part03_qf17_12"
msgid "No way… You actually found it! Gov, give us a hand, will you?"
msgstr ""

msgctxt "mission/single/05-eng/1944_09_20_oosterbeek/narrator/part03_qf17_13"
msgid "I say, bloody hell, she made it! The wheel's gone, but who cares? This is the gun’s last stop anyway. We’re not dragging her out during evac. You’ve done us a real favour, mate."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "mission/single/05-eng/1944_09_20_oosterbeek/narrator/part03_mechanic_01"
msgid "Nice lorry you have here."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "mission/single/05-eng/1944_09_20_oosterbeek/narrator/part03_mechanic_02"
msgid "Don’t even think about nicking it. I know your type, Polak. What do you want?"
msgstr ""

msgctxt "mission/single/05-eng/1944_09_20_oosterbeek/narrator/part03_mechanic_03"
msgid "Relax, I don’t need the whole thing. Just… Part of it. More specifically, I need the wheel. Can you take it off for me?"
msgstr ""

msgctxt "mission/single/05-eng/1944_09_20_oosterbeek/narrator/part03_mechanic_04"
msgid "What the hell do you need a wheel for? …Eh, never mind. I could do it. But let’s say I’d be willing… for a very particular kind of trade. Couple of days back, we were pushing toward Arnhem and I got hit by shrapnel."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "mission/single/05-eng/1944_09_20_oosterbeek/narrator/part03_mechanic_05"
msgid "Thought my lungs exploded. There was a medic who jabbed a syringe in me and the pain just… Vanished. Now it’s the only thing that keeps me from screaming every time I move."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "mission/single/05-eng/1944_09_20_oosterbeek/narrator/part03_mechanic_07"
msgid "We are running short on morphine but I think I know where you might get some. Jerry has a supply stash not far from here. It’s in a broken down ammo trailer near the entrance."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "mission/single/05-eng/1944_09_20_oosterbeek/narrator/part03_mechanic_09"
msgid "Can you lend me one of your Jeeps to tow it out?"
msgstr ""

msgctxt "mission/single/05-eng/1944_09_20_oosterbeek/narrator/part03_mechanic_10"
msgid "Hell no. That trailer might go up any second, and the Major said no risking the transport. We still need to get our arses out of here. But if you find anything usable in there, bring it here."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "mission/single/05-eng/1944_09_20_oosterbeek/narrator/part03_near_truck"
msgid "That’s the lorry I am looking for. Let’s try our luck talking to the mechanic."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "mission/single/05-eng/1944_09_20_oosterbeek/narrator/part03_near_trailer"
msgid "This trailer is still loaded with ammunition, I have to be careful."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "mission/single/05-eng/1944_09_20_oosterbeek/narrator/part03_trailer_tow_hint"
msgid "The red tractor over there might help me to tow the trailer."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "mission/single/05-eng/1944_09_20_oosterbeek/narrator/part03_board_tractor_no_fuel"
msgid "Cholera… The tank is empty. Need to find petrol to refuel it."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "mission/single/05-eng/1944_09_20_oosterbeek/narrator/part03_tractor_refuelled"
msgid "Should be enough fuel for now."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "mission/single/05-eng/1944_09_20_oosterbeek/narrator/part03_board_tractor_with_fuel"
msgid "Now we talk. This thing is capable of towing light emplacements."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "mission/single/05-eng/1944_09_20_oosterbeek/narrator/part03_board_trailer"
msgid "It won’t budge, the wheel is damaged. Maybe I could tow this thing away."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "mission/single/05-eng/1944_09_20_oosterbeek/narrator/part03_trailer_moving"
msgid "Świetnie, now I can the reach Szwaby's treasure."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "mission/single/05-eng/1944_09_20_oosterbeek/narrator/part03_has_wheel"
msgid "Good, now I can bring this wheel to the artillerymen."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "mission/single/05-eng/1944_09_20_oosterbeek/narrator/part03_side_completed"
msgid "Think that’s all. Let’s report to the Major now."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "mission/single/05-eng/1944_09_20_oosterbeek/narrator/part03_civ_01"
msgid "Dziękuję… Ah… Bedankt… It is very good eating. And I really like how beautiful here around. Even my hometown did not look so good before the war as your bombed town right now."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "mission/single/05-eng/1944_09_20_oosterbeek/narrator/cutscene/report_01"
msgid "At ease, lieutenant. Good to see you back in one piece."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "mission/single/05-eng/1944_09_20_oosterbeek/narrator/cutscene/report_02"
msgid "We received tragic news while you were away. The garrison of Lieutenant Colonel Frost in Arnhem had capitulated. I am afraid we shall not wait for anyone from that city to reach us. To avoid their fate, I have made a decision to evacuate our people tonight."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "mission/single/05-eng/1944_09_20_oosterbeek/narrator/cutscene/report_03"
msgid "We will move out under cover of darkness to avoid unnecessary attention. You are needed in a recon role, Lieutenant. The Polish forces with boats are going to wait for you at the river. You have to meet them and give us a signal to begin the evacuation."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "mission/single/05-eng/1944_09_20_oosterbeek/narrator/cutscene/report_04"
msgid "We are going to put an end to this folly operation we call Market Garden and save our wounded and starved men. In the meantime…"
msgstr ""

msgctxt "mission/single/05-eng/1944_09_20_oosterbeek/narrator/cutscene/report_05"
msgid "Mortar! Get down!"
msgstr ""

msgctxt "mission/single/05-eng/1944_09_20_oosterbeek/narrator/part04_01"
msgid "That mortar’s coming from the next district over. Damn things's got a clear line on us."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "mission/single/05-eng/1944_09_20_oosterbeek/narrator/part04_02"
msgid "We need it silenced before it reduces this hotel to rubble. Move swiftly."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "mission/single/05-eng/1944_09_20_oosterbeek/narrator/part04_03"
msgid "Lieutenant Kowalczyk, you’ve got some of your countrymen without a unit. They’re yours now. Make good use of them."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "mission/single/05-eng/1944_09_20_oosterbeek/narrator/part04_04"
msgid "Good. One problem off the board."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "mission/single/05-eng/1944_09_20_oosterbeek/narrator/part04_05"
msgid "Heads up, they’re pushing through from the east. Lieutenant, I need you on that flank. We have reserves nearby, but without support, they won’t hold."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "mission/single/05-eng/1944_09_20_oosterbeek/narrator/part04_06"
msgid "They have decided to go full scale, ha? Hold your ground, people!"
msgstr ""

msgctxt "mission/single/05-eng/1944_09_20_oosterbeek/narrator/part04_07"
msgid "O, kurwa… Tiger is coming from the north, take care of it!"
msgstr ""

msgctxt "mission/single/05-eng/1944_09_20_oosterbeek/narrator/part04_07_qf17"
msgid "You gave us a hand with the 17-pounder. Now it’s our turn. At your command, Lieutenant."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "mission/single/05-eng/1944_09_20_oosterbeek/narrator/part04_08"
msgid "A second Tiger? Ja pierdolę… Szwaby must having a laugh."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "mission/single/05-eng/1944_09_20_oosterbeek/narrator/part04_09"
msgid "We did it men, they are falling back. Hopefully that was their last attack for today. Get some rest. The Major said we are moving out tonight."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "mission/single/05-eng/1944_09_20_oosterbeek/narrator/cutscene/scout_01"
msgid "…No way she treated you like that! The hell she’s thinking she is?"
msgstr ""

msgctxt "mission/single/05-eng/1944_09_20_oosterbeek/narrator/cutscene/scout_02"
msgid "Well… Women… Can’t live with ‘em, can’t live without ‘em."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "mission/single/05-eng/1944_09_20_oosterbeek/narrator/cutscene/scout_03"
msgid "The break is over, lads. We have to move to the finish line."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "mission/single/05-eng/1944_09_20_oosterbeek/narrator/part05_01"
msgid "Our Polish friends are still waiting for us to arrive at the shore to get us out of here. We lost contact with them this evening and they probably don’t even know we’re still alive."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "mission/single/05-eng/1944_09_20_oosterbeek/narrator/part05_02"
msgid "They won’t be waiting for too long for us, Szwaby are pushing them just as bad as they do to us. We have to let them know we’re still here as soon as possible. It’s now or never."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "mission/single/05-eng/1944_09_20_oosterbeek/narrator/part05_03"
msgid "The Szwaby are in the village! Don’t waste time on killing all of them, we have to hurry! Our primary objective is to let the people on the other side know we’re still alive!"
msgstr ""

msgctxt "mission/single/05-eng/1944_09_20_oosterbeek/narrator/part05_04"
msgid "Sir?.. There’s no one there… The bloody evac team is not there!"
msgstr ""

msgctxt "mission/single/05-eng/1944_09_20_oosterbeek/narrator/part05_05"
msgid "Co do diabła?.."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "mission/single/05-eng/1944_09_20_oosterbeek/narrator/part05_06"
msgid "Lieutenant, we've finally made contact with the evacuation team. They’re still holding, but had to pull back east under pressure. There’s a village nearby crawling with German vehicles. If we don’t act fast, they’ll compromise the entire operation."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "mission/single/05-eng/1944_09_20_oosterbeek/narrator/part05_07"
msgid "The evac team won’t last much longer. Those vehicles must be taken out as soon as possible. That’s your priority, Lieutenant Kowalczyk."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "mission/single/05-eng/1944_09_20_oosterbeek/narrator/part05_08"
msgid "The village is swarming with infantry as well. I’m sending a platoon your way, they’ll draw attention from the enemy. Focus on knocking out those damn vehicles."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "mission/single/05-eng/1944_09_20_oosterbeek/narrator/part05_09"
msgid "I wish I could give you more. But these are the last combat-ready men we’ve got. Remember what you're fighting for. Behind you are dozens of wounded, starving men who haven’t slept in days. You’re their last chance, Lieutenant. I trust you. Don’t let them down."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "mission/single/05-eng/1944_09_20_oosterbeek/narrator/part05_10"
msgid "All vehicles destroyed! Let’s get the fuck out of here!"
msgstr ""

msgctxt "mission/single/05-eng/1944_09_20_oosterbeek/narrator/part05_captured_broken_vehicle"
msgid "How is this thing still even driving without wheels and transmission? Szwaby should have rather made that many civilian cars instead of tanks."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "mission/single/05-eng/1944_09_20_oosterbeek/narrator/part05_vehicle_destroyed_01"
msgid "Good, one vehicle down."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "mission/single/05-eng/1944_09_20_oosterbeek/narrator/part05_vehicle_destroyed_02"
msgid "Two vehicles down but we have to get rid of them faster!"
msgstr ""

msgctxt "mission/single/05-eng/1944_09_20_oosterbeek/narrator/part05_vehicle_destroyed_03"
msgid "Three out of four! One to go!"
msgstr ""

msgctxt "mission/single/05-eng/1944_09_20_oosterbeek/narrator/part05_pl_swim"
msgid "Where do you think you’re going?! We have a job to do!"
msgstr ""

msgctxt "mission/single/05-eng/1944_09_20_oosterbeek/narrator/cutscene/outro_01"
msgid "That’s the last cab. Everyone, get on the board! Hope we didn’t leave someone behind."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "mission/single/05-eng/1944_09_20_oosterbeek/narrator/cutscene/outro_02"
msgid "Bloody hell, get us out of here! They're already waiting!"
msgstr ""

msgctxt "mission/single/05-eng/1944_09_20_oosterbeek/narrator/cutscene/outro_03"
msgid "Oi, wait for us, you bastards!"
msgstr ""

msgctxt "mission/single/05-eng/1944_09_20_oosterbeek/narrator/part01_extraction_reached_one_man"
msgid "We’re almost there. But we should not leave our men behind."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "mission/single/05-eng/1944_09_20_oosterbeek/narrator/part01_extraction_reached"
msgid "Good, we made it through. Let’s get the hell out."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "mission/single/05-eng/1944_09_20_oosterbeek/narrator/stealth_light_hint"
msgid "Half of the town is in flames. Let’s avoid these spots and sneak through patrols like shadows."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "mission/single/05-eng/1944_09_20_oosterbeek/narrator/stealth_take_body"
msgid "We should not leave the corpses, other Szwaby will find them."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "mission/single/05-eng/1944_09_20_oosterbeek/narrator/stealth_stabbed"
msgid "Nice three-point shot."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "mission/single/05-eng/1944_09_20_oosterbeek/narrator/stealth_saw_body"
msgid "This skurwiel saw the body! Kill him now!"
msgstr ""

msgctxt "mission/single/05-eng/1944_09_20_oosterbeek/narrator/stealth_pl_spotted"
msgid "Cholera, they see us. Open fire!"
msgstr ""

msgctxt "mission/single/05-eng/1944_09_20_oosterbeek/narrator/stealth_all_enemies_dead"
msgid "I think it was the last of them. Let’s keep moving, chlopaki."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "mission/single/05-eng/1944_09_20_oosterbeek/ui/hint_take_body"
msgid "To carry the dead body,\n\nclick <c(B29557)>Take</c> action in <c(B29557)>Item Options</c> on the control panel. \n\nTo drop the body, select any weapon at your unit."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "mission/single/05-eng/1944_09_20_oosterbeek/ui/hint_stealth_evac"
msgid "Only 1 soldier must reach the British perimeter if you decide for a stealth approach."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "mission/single/05-eng/1944_09_20_oosterbeek/ui/hint_knifes"
msgid "Use <c(B29557)>throwing knifes</c> to eliminate enemies silently. \n\nYou can throw them more effectively in <c(B29557)>direct control</c>."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "mission/single/05-eng/1944_09_20_oosterbeek/ui/hint_side_quest"
msgid "Optional activities will not be available after reporting to HQ. \n\nTo report to HQ, click on the specific button in the reinforcements tab. This button is shown when you're near to the hotel building."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "mission/single/05-eng/1944_09_20_oosterbeek/ui/hint_refuel_01"
msgid "Find a <c(B29557)>gas can</c> to refuel the tractor."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "mission/single/05-eng/1944_09_20_oosterbeek/ui/hint_refuel_02"
msgid "To <c(B29557)>fill the canister</c>, put it in your character's hands. \n\nYou can do this by double-clicking on the item in the inventory. \n\nWhile the canister is in your hand, <c(B29557)>hover over any vehicle</c>. \n\nA can icon will appear. Right-click to fill the canister."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "mission/single/05-eng/1944_09_20_oosterbeek/ui/hint_refuel_03"
msgid "To <c(B29557)>refuel the tractor from a canister</c>, \n\nhover over the tractor while the character is carrying a canister full of gas. A funnel icon will appear. \n\nClick the right mouse button and the character will transfer the gas."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "mission/single/05-eng/1944_09_20_oosterbeek/ui/hint_part01_choice"
msgid "You can select either <c(B29557)>Stealth</c> or <c(B29557)>Combat</c> approach for this mission phase.\n\nClick at one of the options at the <c(B29557)>reinforcements tab</c>."
msgstr ""

